You know I could have done at
least with a bit of grapefruit.

02:14.060 --> 02:19.539
Or a croissant or some
buck's fizz to fuck me up nicely

02:19.540 --> 02:20.940
some mentholated cigarettes.

02:20.941 --> 02:23.539
PHONE RINGS

02:23.540 --> 02:24.258
Hi, Dad.

02:24.259 --> 02:25.580
'Alex. Right.

02:25.581 --> 02:28.339
'How you getting on? You all
set for the move next week?'

02:28.340 --> 02:29.060
Yeah.

02:29.061 --> 02:32.779
'Good. Good.
Remember to label everything.

02:32.780 --> 02:33.820
'D'you hear me Alex?'

02:33.821 --> 02:35.019
Yeah I will.

02:35.020 --> 02:36.539
'Is she there?'

02:36.540 --> 02:39.219
She's... she's still sleeping.

02:39.220 --> 02:41.580
'Well the home are expecting her
next Wednesday, so just remind her.'

02:41.581 --> 02:42.939
Yes. OK.

02:42.940 --> 02:44.378
'Remember to label everything.'

02:44.379 --> 02:45.020
I'm doing it, Dad.

02:45.021 --> 02:46.580
'You better be.'

02:49.580 --> 02:51.499
Silly old twat.

02:51.500 --> 02:53.219
He's your son, Gran.

02:53.220 --> 02:57.699
Did he at least remember
to wish you good luck for today?

02:57.700 --> 03:01.580
No, well never mind.
You don't need any.

03:29.940 --> 03:32.099
You and I have a lot in common.

03:32.100 --> 03:34.259
Your first day.

03:34.260 --> 03:35.260
Mine too.

03:37.500 --> 03:39.739
Be confident. Assertive.

03:39.740 --> 03:41.339
Give them a chink of light

03:41.340 --> 03:45.139
and they'll take you to
the cleaners, Boyo.

03:45.140 --> 03:48.619
Yeah, I'm used to being the new boy.
I'll get by.

03:48.620 --> 03:52.979
Here we are. Information
Communication Technology.

03:52.980 --> 03:54.779
Your first class.

03:54.780 --> 03:58.139
Pretty sure
I didn't sign up for that.

03:58.140 --> 04:02.420
Yes, your father phoned.
He changed some things around.

04:05.100 --> 04:06.460
Right.

04:09.140 --> 04:14.419
Class, this is Alex Henley.
He's new today.

04:14.420 --> 04:19.738
So go, take him to your bosoms
and show him a thundering good time.

04:19.740 --> 04:23.460
Doug. Problem with the flies.

04:24.740 --> 04:26.220
Goodness!

04:26.221 --> 04:29.779
I do apologise.
We don't want to see that, look you.

04:29.780 --> 04:32.979
There's another thing.
I'm not Doug any more.

04:32.980 --> 04:36.619
I'm also the head teacher
and that means you have to call me

04:36.620 --> 04:40.579
by my proper name
Mr Cyhoeddus-Gwalchmai.

04:40.580 --> 04:42.259
LAUGHTER

04:42.260 --> 04:45.539
Yes, all right, very amusing.

04:45.540 --> 04:46.780
All right settle down.

05:44.500 --> 05:46.458
Rich is supposed to
be my project partner.

05:46.459 --> 05:47.740
His girlfriend just died.

05:47.741 --> 05:50.619
I don't think he cares
about your fucking coursework.

05:50.620 --> 05:51.138
I suppose.

05:51.139 --> 05:53.258
He'll be back
when he's got over things.

05:53.259 --> 05:55.420
Just get Franky to do it for you.
Everyone else does.

05:57.420 --> 06:00.219
Mate, I'm really really sorry.

06:00.220 --> 06:01.580
What the fuck was that for?!

06:01.581 --> 06:03.900
It's numbers mate. Only numbers.

06:24.500 --> 06:27.139
Mini.
How long is this going to go on for?

06:27.140 --> 06:29.179
I called you four times last night.

06:29.180 --> 06:29.780
I was busy.

06:29.781 --> 06:30.859
With what?

06:30.860 --> 06:32.900
Bloody hell, Mum.
I was doing coursework.

06:32.901 --> 06:34.779
You don't need to avoid me.

06:34.780 --> 06:36.738
Why would I be avoiding you?

06:36.739 --> 06:37.618
Because you don't want
to talk about her.

06:37.619 --> 06:39.420
That's not it.

06:39.421 --> 06:42.939
Come on, Mins. We have to see each
other every day. Gracey would say...

06:42.940 --> 06:44.620
I'm not avoiding you, OK?

06:51.380 --> 06:52.420
Hey.

06:52.421 --> 06:54.179
Yeah?

06:54.180 --> 06:54.940
What's your problem?

06:56.020 --> 06:58.299
Punching people?

06:58.300 --> 06:59.058
I don't have a problem.

06:59.059 --> 07:00.580
So why did you do it?

07:00.581 --> 07:01.779
Numbers.

07:01.780 --> 07:02.860
What?

07:02.861 --> 07:05.139
If you live by this,
everything's random.

07:05.140 --> 07:08.020
So what are these numbers
telling you now?

07:22.540 --> 07:23.780
Alex.

07:25.300 --> 07:26.819
Liv.

07:26.820 --> 07:29.299
Pleased to meet you.

07:29.300 --> 07:31.659
I never even knew this was here.

07:31.660 --> 07:33.620
I only live, like, 200 yards away.

07:33.621 --> 07:36.339
Yeah. It's funny what you see
and what you don't see.

07:36.340 --> 07:37.740
Like you and your friend
aren't speaking to each other.

07:37.741 --> 07:39.699
What?

07:39.700 --> 07:43.579
And why you're pouring a quarter of
whisky into your coffee before noon.

07:43.580 --> 07:44.700
I'm an alkie.

07:44.701 --> 07:46.019
I'm a psycho.

07:46.020 --> 07:47.818
With a magic dice.

07:47.819 --> 07:49.319
Everything about me's magic.

07:50.140 --> 07:53.139
Yeah, you should try it ...
keeps things buzzy.

07:53.140 --> 07:54.260
You reckon?

07:54.261 --> 07:57.420
What was the name
of your friend that died?

07:59.300 --> 08:00.500
Grace.

08:01.620 --> 08:04.779
You want to meet the wicked witch?

08:18.581 --> 08:20.700
Hello? Gran?

08:26.260 --> 08:28.299
She'll be here somewhere.

08:28.300 --> 08:29.939
She does exist, right?

08:29.940 --> 08:32.059
Pretty sure she does, yeah.

08:36.100 --> 08:38.899
Hello, Alex.

08:38.900 --> 08:41.380
Are you wanting to come
out of there or...?

08:42.860 --> 08:44.980
No. I'm fine where I am.

08:46.100 --> 08:49.540
I was joking.

08:51.100 --> 08:52.340
Sure, Gran.

08:54.380 --> 08:56.819
I must have got a bit confused.

08:56.820 --> 08:58.740
This is Liv.

09:01.540 --> 09:03.819
She's a girl.

09:03.820 --> 09:06.739
Yep, that's right. She's a girl.

09:06.740 --> 09:10.180
I like the colour of you.

09:11.580 --> 09:13.260
Thank you.

09:15.500 --> 09:19.660
Beans for three. There you go, Gran.

09:23.060 --> 09:26.259
Very handsome. Wouldn't you say?

09:26.260 --> 09:27.779
Of course I am.

09:27.780 --> 09:33.099
It's the cheekbones. He gets them
from his Grandad William.

09:33.100 --> 09:36.220
He was an extremely virile man.

09:38.100 --> 09:39.419
Right.

09:39.420 --> 09:42.579
I was only 13 when I met him.

09:42.580 --> 09:45.499
You were 23, Gran.
Don't go overboard.

09:45.500 --> 09:49.139
Yes. There was a dance.

09:49.140 --> 09:54.299
He was all dressed up in uniform.

09:54.300 --> 09:58.739
He comes over, with a shiny penny
in his right hand.

09:58.740 --> 10:00.739
He throws it up, catches it.

10:00.740 --> 10:01.940
And he says...

10:03.100 --> 10:07.299
Heads ... we have a dance
then we go our ways.

10:07.300 --> 10:09.699
Tails ... you come with me

10:09.700 --> 10:14.219
and we'll get wed at Dover
as soon as you like.

10:14.220 --> 10:15.779
And you married him?

10:15.780 --> 10:20.260
Well, I screwed him senseless
for quite a while.

10:22.780 --> 10:26.779
You know, they're
going to put me in a home.

10:26.780 --> 10:30.579
Alex is packing my things away,
getting me ready.

10:30.580 --> 10:32.540
Why are they putting you in a home?

10:33.740 --> 10:35.380
Because I'm losing my mind.

10:36.500 --> 10:39.619
Alex is doing
a nasty little job for his dad.

10:39.620 --> 10:42.099
I'm just trying
to look after you, Gran.

10:42.100 --> 10:48.780
Yes, well, tell your dad to keep his
poisonous little hands off my house.

10:58.940 --> 11:00.820
You better go.

11:04.300 --> 11:08.059
So, you had the baked beans,
a glass of coke...

11:08.060 --> 11:09.100
That's about Â£3.50.

11:09.101 --> 11:11.779
And there wasn't even a dessert.

11:11.780 --> 11:14.059
Maybe next time, yeah?

11:14.060 --> 11:18.179
Some of us are going to the pub.
Latimers. And... er...

11:18.180 --> 11:19.020
you should come along.

11:19.021 --> 11:20.420
Maybe.

11:21.740 --> 11:23.660
Sure.

11:36.980 --> 11:42.819
"15th September, 1964.
13 miles off St Kilda.

11:42.820 --> 11:45.419
"The sea was rough, Force 9 today,

11:45.420 --> 11:49.059
"but the Captain was determined
to run for Norway

11:49.060 --> 11:51.659
"and refused to put in
at Greenock."

11:51.660 --> 11:52.700
Idiot.

11:54.860 --> 11:57.699
"One engine is down
and we are taking in water,

11:57.700 --> 12:01.979
"but I have taken bets from eight
of the crew against making it.

12:01.980 --> 12:04.739
"If we are rescued,
I will be a rich man."

12:04.740 --> 12:07.220
PHONE RINGS

12:51.380 --> 12:52.340
Hi.

12:53.580 --> 12:56.619
Anybody want a shot?

12:56.620 --> 12:57.660
Look I don't want any trouble,
mate, all right?

12:57.661 --> 12:59.819
No. A shot. You know?

12:59.820 --> 13:02.060
Or a... something.

13:10.020 --> 13:11.939
Take that as a yes, then.

13:11.940 --> 13:13.779
I'll give you a hand.

13:13.780 --> 13:15.459
Nah, it's OK. I've got it.

13:15.460 --> 13:18.419
You got a new friend, then?

13:18.420 --> 13:20.338
He's a nice guy.

13:20.339 --> 13:21.460
He's a whack job.
Have you seen what he's done to me?

13:21.461 --> 13:24.060
Just give him a break.

13:26.220 --> 13:28.380
We don't need any new friends.

13:30.380 --> 13:32.380
I'm fine.

13:39.300 --> 13:41.539
Whoa, that's a lot of cash.

13:41.540 --> 13:45.339
Yeah, I like cash.
I like the feel of it in me hand.

13:45.340 --> 13:47.339
I see that.

13:47.340 --> 13:48.980
Cheers, mate.

13:51.180 --> 13:53.300
What was she like? Grace.

13:56.420 --> 14:00.499
Mate. You're cool and everything.
But leave that alone.

14:00.500 --> 14:01.620
All right?

14:01.621 --> 14:02.780
Yeah, sure.

14:13.060 --> 14:17.020
Alex, this is, er, Mini, Alo,
Nick and Franky.

14:29.940 --> 14:31.620
You're boring.

14:56.860 --> 15:01.059
You're way too cool
to be her friend.

15:01.060 --> 15:04.579
It's a tough job,
but someone's got to do it.

15:04.580 --> 15:06.860
Her boyfriend's
getting a bit anxious.

15:08.340 --> 15:11.339
That's just Alo.
He's not her boyfriend, trust me.

15:11.340 --> 15:14.379
I guess you guys
are a little on edge, yeah?

15:14.380 --> 15:17.660
We're, er... yeah.

15:21.740 --> 15:24.060
This was probably a mistake.

15:29.460 --> 15:32.219
All right, fuck it. I'm dancing.

15:32.220 --> 15:33.140
Liv?

15:34.340 --> 15:35.659
Franky?

15:35.660 --> 15:37.580
Come on, yeah?

15:40.220 --> 15:41.298
Yeah?

15:41.299 --> 15:42.338
That's way too gay, mate.

15:42.339 --> 15:43.580
What?!

15:43.581 --> 15:45.939
I'll dance with you.

15:45.940 --> 15:47.939
Yeah, maybe, mate.

15:47.940 --> 15:50.099
PHONE RINGS

15:50.100 --> 15:52.900
Shit! Shit. Sorry.

15:58.860 --> 16:00.979
Fuck it. Come and gay me.

16:02.301 --> 16:04.299
Are you dancing or what?

16:04.300 --> 16:05.340
Yeah.

16:14.780 --> 16:16.860
PHONE RINGS

16:19.020 --> 16:20.099
Hi, Dad.

16:20.100 --> 16:22.099
'Alex. Where are you?'

16:22.100 --> 16:24.979
I'm at home.

16:24.980 --> 16:27.819
'I've been calling the house phone.
Nobody answered.'

16:27.820 --> 16:30.779
Yeah, well, Gran likes
to turn the TV up loud.

16:30.780 --> 16:34.059
'Where are we with her?
Are you packing her stuff?'

16:34.060 --> 16:38.379
Yeah, it's not...
It's not... It's not simple.

16:38.380 --> 16:39.899
'What are you talking about?'

16:39.900 --> 16:40.740
I've been thinking.

16:40.741 --> 16:43.739
'Not your job to think, Alex.
It's your job to act.

16:43.740 --> 16:46.299
'I'm relying on you. OK?'

16:46.300 --> 16:47.339
OK.

16:47.340 --> 16:49.260
'I'll be flying over next week.

16:49.261 --> 16:51.579
'Want it all sorted out by then.
Clear?'

16:51.580 --> 16:52.260
Crystal.

16:52.261 --> 16:55.380
'Good. Say hello
to your gran for me.'

16:57.780 --> 16:59.899
"How are you, Alex?"
"Good, thanks, Dad.

16:59.900 --> 17:01.499
"First day at college today."

17:01.500 --> 17:04.939
"Yeah, how did that go?"
"Really well, thanks.

17:04.940 --> 17:07.659
"I met this really nice girl
and... and she was so..."

17:07.660 --> 17:09.740
And she was so...?

17:11.660 --> 17:13.180
So...

17:15.579 --> 17:17.380
Are you a gambling woman?

17:29.740 --> 17:31.459
Alex, what the fuck?!

17:31.460 --> 17:34.339
Alex. How's it going, you all right?

17:34.340 --> 17:37.220
Good to see you again.
Usual table, yeah?

17:39.220 --> 17:40.859
You know how to play cards?

17:40.860 --> 17:42.019
No.

17:42.020 --> 17:44.380
Shit. That makes two of us.

18:03.660 --> 18:05.060
Right, then.

18:12.980 --> 18:14.140
Rock'n'roll.

18:33.140 --> 18:34.180
Ace flush.

18:43.540 --> 18:44.820
Full house.

18:51.020 --> 18:53.019
Hey, calm down! Calm down!

18:53.020 --> 18:54.220
What's going on?

18:54.221 --> 18:57.459
They just want to make me a cake.
Celebrate my victory.

18:57.460 --> 18:59.019
He says you're a cheat.

18:59.020 --> 19:01.139
No, no. Not a cheat.

19:01.140 --> 19:02.779
A fucking cheat.

19:02.780 --> 19:05.459
Well, obviously,
I'll take issue with that.

19:05.460 --> 19:06.939
No!

19:06.940 --> 19:10.659
Now, look,
you're scaring my girlfriend.

19:10.660 --> 19:12.579
I don't suppose you know kung fu?

19:12.580 --> 19:13.780
No.

19:13.781 --> 19:15.499
Dear.

19:15.500 --> 19:17.380
You're a fucking tosser.

19:19.500 --> 19:22.380
I'll tell you what.
Let's play tossers, eh?

19:23.700 --> 19:28.299
Call it, go on.
Call tails, I dare you.

19:28.300 --> 19:32.499
For the money?
Then we can part as friends, yeah?

19:32.500 --> 19:34.420
Tails.

19:46.580 --> 19:48.700
Collect the money, Liv.

20:15.820 --> 20:17.780
Run.

20:26.500 --> 20:28.939
Fuck.

20:28.940 --> 20:30.540
You're just...

20:30.541 --> 20:31.819
I'm a cheat.

20:31.820 --> 20:35.339
Yeah. You're a fucking cheat.

20:35.340 --> 20:35.740
Jesus!

20:35.741 --> 20:37.860
PHONE RINGS

20:45.940 --> 20:49.219
Shit, sorry. I've got to...

20:49.220 --> 20:50.659
My gran, you know?

20:50.660 --> 20:52.660
Taxi's on me.

20:57.820 --> 20:59.459
Here, er, take some of this.

20:59.460 --> 21:00.700
OK, but...

21:00.701 --> 21:03.700
I've had a lovely time.
See you at college, yeah?

21:08.500 --> 21:10.419
Alex...

21:10.420 --> 21:12.739
you don't have to be shy.

21:12.740 --> 21:14.020
I know.

21:17.820 --> 21:19.140
Take care, yeah?

22:08.100 --> 22:11.299
You need to update your profile pic.

22:11.300 --> 22:15.459
It was a little while back.

22:15.460 --> 22:17.780
In a galaxy far, far away. Yeah.

22:21.180 --> 22:24.420
It was all right though? Yeah?

22:25.420 --> 22:26.900
Sure.

22:35.380 --> 22:37.259
What's this?

22:37.260 --> 22:39.339
You're a nice kid. Take it.

22:39.340 --> 22:41.139
I'm not a fucking rent boy.

22:41.140 --> 22:45.540
And even if I was, 20 quid?!
Seriously?

22:46.780 --> 22:49.299
You're missing the point, mate.

22:49.300 --> 22:52.940
Just for a moment,
everything was meaningless.

22:54.740 --> 22:55.740
Well.

23:03.220 --> 23:05.739
Cheers.

23:05.740 --> 23:10.539
And erm... you need to see someone
about your dental hygiene problem.

23:10.540 --> 23:12.939
I'm not telling you that
to be cruel,

23:12.940 --> 23:15.420
I'm telling you because it's true.

23:36.260 --> 23:38.658
Alex, I need you to call me back.

23:38.659 --> 23:39.900
PHONE RINGS

23:39.901 --> 23:45.099
Alex, why
aren't you answering your phone?

23:45.100 --> 23:48.139
Alex, your behaviour
is concerning me.

23:48.140 --> 23:50.780
'I'm waiting to hear from you.
OK? Call me.'

23:56.100 --> 23:57.980
What's your stupid card
say today then?

24:14.860 --> 24:16.619
One.

24:16.620 --> 24:19.579
Break and enter a stranger's house.

24:19.580 --> 24:21.979
Liv. Liv, is anyone in?

24:21.980 --> 24:22.940
No.

24:27.620 --> 24:30.299
Definitely a serial killer.

24:30.300 --> 24:33.099
Fucking 'ell! This place stinks!

24:33.100 --> 24:35.860
Yeah. What a dirty bastard.

24:38.020 --> 24:40.059
Exotic porno collection.

24:40.060 --> 24:41.420
Whoah!

24:50.660 --> 24:53.099
Let's fuck with this guy's head.

24:53.100 --> 24:56.139
You're not going to take
a dump on the bed or something?

24:56.140 --> 24:57.660
Exact opposite.

25:22.260 --> 25:23.180
Liv, I'm...

25:23.181 --> 25:24.579
DOOR OPENS

25:24.580 --> 25:25.860
Fuck!

25:34.100 --> 25:35.540
Whoo-hoo!

25:37.580 --> 25:38.860
LAUGHTER

25:41.860 --> 25:42.980
My dad's here.

25:55.820 --> 25:56.780
Hi, Dad.

25:58.100 --> 25:59.260
Hello, Alex.

26:02.300 --> 26:03.780
What are you doing?

26:03.781 --> 26:07.940
I'm doing what you were incapable
of doing. Sorting things out.

26:10.180 --> 26:14.259
Look, we don't need to do this.
She doesn't have to go into a home.

26:14.260 --> 26:18.459
I'll quit college and I'll get
a job. I'll... I'll look after her.

26:18.460 --> 26:18.978
No.

26:18.979 --> 26:20.180
Why not?

26:20.181 --> 26:22.459
Because that's my decision.

26:22.460 --> 26:23.740
No, that's not an answer!

26:23.741 --> 26:27.139
If you're going to get emotional,
I won't discuss it with you.

26:27.140 --> 26:30.099
You're not discussing it
with me anyway!

26:30.100 --> 26:31.620
We all need to take a break!

26:35.140 --> 26:36.700
Calm down.

26:40.260 --> 26:44.099
Meet me tonight for dinner, OK,
and pack this stuff away.

26:44.100 --> 26:45.659
Or I will.

26:45.660 --> 26:47.619
Mum? I'll come back later.

26:47.620 --> 26:51.499
We don't need you.
William's looking after me.

26:51.500 --> 26:55.420
No, Mum.
Dad died a very long time ago.

26:57.940 --> 26:59.900
